Levis Mwalimu, 34, who was among the six people killed in last Thursday s Mandera attack, will be buried tomorrow at his Chigojoni home, Kilifi county.He worked with Islamic Relief Kenya in Mandera. Mary Masika, 35, Mwalimu s widow, on Monday said her husband was not happy working in Mandera because of the terror attacks and was contemplating abandoning the contract. When he came home three weeks ago, he said he would not renew the contract. He wanted to return home, she said. Mwalimu was on a one-year contract that started last December.